Ellaktor to Sell 7.1% Stake in European Goldfieds to Qatar

-- B y   M a r c u s   B e n s a s s o n
-- 
2011-10-01T18:22:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-01/ellaktor-to-sell-7-1-stake-in-european-goldfieds-to-qatar.html
Ellaktor SA (ELLAKTOR) , Greeceâ€™s largest
construction company, agreed to sell a 7.1 percent stake in
 European Goldfields Ltd. (EGU)  to Qatar Holdings LLC, the company said
in an e-mailed statement.  Athens-based Ellaktor sold the stake for C$130 million
($125 million) and will retain a 12.2 percent holding in the
company, the statement said.   The Qatari company has an option to buy a further 9.4
million shares in European Goldfields at C$13 a share and will
also provide a $600 million financing facility for development
of a gold mine in northern Greece, the statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
